# Rehla DBX Tools Persistent Context

- Treat this project as `rehla_dbx_tools` first in naming, examples, and user guidance.
- Prefer the distribution/import names:
  - `pip install rehla-dbx-tools`
  - `from rehla_dbx_tools import DatabricksApiClient`
- Default to simple end-user flows before advanced config:
  - `DatabricksApiClient.simple(host=..., token=...)`
  - token-optional fallbacks (env, browser+prompt, Windows SSO)
- Keep snippets minimal and practical:
  - import package
  - host
  - token (or optional auth fallback)
  - account_id only when account APIs are used
  - function call
- When explaining errors, start with fastest fix and avoid overcomplicating setup.
